                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4904,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/02/237301566/6dfc1c5f5f69b627eb5428b304e30377_6627017400427115689.png",
                      "name": "Осиал",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Vibrant Harriers Aloft in Spring Breeze",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/c69d6b2196ba4661ae932f5f35403da6_5979509907257045237.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Mountain Shaper and Moon Carver visited Liyue Harbor during the Lantern Rite to meet with Cloud Retainer. They disguised themselves as mortals, Houzhang and Jiehu, so that people would not recognize them. The Traveler and Paimon initially mistook the Adepti for Treasure Hoarders, and they had to prove they were illuminated beasts. Mountain Shaper said he had once come to the harbor to collect karst crawlers' seeds, and the young people of Liyue were pestering him. In the end, Streetward Rambler had to save her friend. He also said that he borrows a cooking machine from Cloud Retainer and cooks food, hiding the machine whenever he sees the Adepti.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "During Cloud Retainer's kite-flying master class on Mt. Aocang, the Moon Carver and Mountain Shaper were flying a kite on a nearby mountain. The kite accidentally ended up on Mt. Aocang, and they had to meet Cloud Retainer, who immediately recognized them as old friends. Later, the Adepti participated in Cloud Retainer's plan to help a young man from Chenyu Vale, Gaming, reunite with his father. They pretended to be the Treasure Hoarders and distracted Gaming while the Traveler and Paimon followed the plan and took Gaming's father away.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/29/124137736/e55553ace2ef718946915fc5424b250e_8751539331172708844.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "At the Lantern Rite, which honored the memory of the deceased Yaksha, Menogias, Mountain Shaper and Moon Carver recalled that as a master of handicrafts, it would not have been difficult for Menogias to create kites. If he was still alive, he could have opened his own kite shop, which would have brought him not only great profit but also even greater respect. And if Menogias, as before, did not dare to get involved in human affairs, he could have entrusted the sale of kites to them. Thus, while thinking about how they would celebrate their success together in wonderful company with a bottle of wine, the Adepti were filled with happy memories and enjoyed the beauty of the harbor beyond Menogias.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
